type of the memory."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"aside","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A trivial type can be copied with just a bit-for-bit copy without"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"any indirection or reference-counting operations. Generally, native"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Swift types that do not contain strong or weak references or other"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"forms of indirection are trivial, as are imported C structs and enums."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"Note","style":"note"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If you need to store into memory a copy of a value of a type that isn’t","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"trivial, you cannot use the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"storeBytes(of:toByteOffset:as:)"},{"type":"text","text":" method."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Instead, you must know either initialize the memory or,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"if you know the memory was already bound to ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"type"},{"text":", assign to the memory.","type":"text"}]}]}],"sections":[],"variants":[{"paths":["/documentation/swift/slice/storebytes(of:tobyteoffset:as:)"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Stores a value’s bytes into the buffer pointer slice’s raw memory at the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"specified byte offset."}],"metadata":{"conformance":{"availabilityPrefix":[{"type":"text","text":"Available when"}],"conformancePrefix":[{"type":"text","text":"Conforms when"}],"constraints":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Base"},{"type":"text","text":" is "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"UnsafeMutableRawBufferPointer"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},"roleHeading":"Instance Method","extendedModule":"Swift","title":"storeBytes(of:toByteOffset:as:)","modules